113#define MODE_SCRIPT 1
114#define MODE_CMDDUMP 2
115#define MODE_CMDFLUSH 3
116#define MODE_PROMISC 4
117#define MODE_STDIN 5

121int f_forever = 0;
122int f_all = 0;
123int f_verbose = 0;
124int f_mode = 0;
125int f_cmddump = 0;
126int f_policy = 0;
127int f_hexdump = 0;
128int f_tflag = 0;
129int f_notreally = 0;
130int f_withports = 0;
131#ifdef HAVE_PFKEY_POLICY_PRIORITY
132int last_msg_type;
133uint32_t last_priority;

136int f_rfcmode = 1;
137#define RK_OPTS "rk"
138#else
139static int f_rkwarn = 0;
140#define RK_OPTS ""
141static void
142rkwarn(void)
143{
144 if (!f_rkwarn) {
145 f_rkwarn = 1;
146 printf("warning: -r and -k options are not supported in this environment\n");
147 }
148}
149#endif

152int exit_now;

155static void
156usage(int only_version)
157{
158 printf("setkey @(#) %s (%s)\n", TOP_PACKAGE_STRING, TOP_PACKAGE_URL);
159 if (!only_version) {
160 printf("usage: setkey [-v" RK_OPTS "] file ...\n");
161 printf(" setkey [-nv" RK_OPTS "] -c\n");
162 printf(" setkey [-nv" RK_OPTS "] -f filename\n");
163 printf(" setkey [-Palpv" RK_OPTS "] -D\n");
164 printf(" setkey [-Pv] -F\n");
165 printf(" setkey [-H] -x\n");
166 printf(" setkey [-V] [-h]\n");
167 }
168 exit(1);
169}
170
171int
172main(int argc, char **argv)
173{
174 FILE *fp = stdin;
175 int c;
176
177 if (argc == 1) {
178 usage(0);
179 }
180
181 thiszone = gmt2local(0);
182
183 while ((c = getopt(argc, argv, "acdf:HlnvxDFPphVrk?")) != -1) {
184 switch (c) {
185 case 'c':
186 f_mode = MODE_STDIN;
187#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
188 /* disable filename completion */
189 rl_bind_key('\t', rl_insert);
190#endif
191 break;
192 case 'f':
193 f_mode = MODE_SCRIPT;
194 if (strcmp(optarg, "-") == 0) {
195 fp = stdin;
196 } else if ((fp = fopen(optarg, "r")) == NULL) {
197 err(1, "Can't open `%s'", optarg);
198 }
199 break;
200 case 'D':
201 f_mode = MODE_CMDDUMP;
202 break;
203 case 'F':
204 f_mode = MODE_CMDFLUSH;
205 break;
206 case 'a':
207 f_all = 1;
208 break;
209 case 'l':
210 f_forever = 1;
211 break;
212 case 'n':
213 f_notreally = 1;
214 break;
215#ifdef __NetBSD__
216 case 'h':
217#endif
218 case 'H':
219 f_hexdump = 1;
220 break;
221 case 'x':
222 f_mode = MODE_PROMISC;
223 f_tflag++;
224 break;
225 case 'P':
226 f_policy = 1;
227 break;
228 case 'p':
229 f_withports = 1;
230 break;
231 case 'v':
232 f_verbose = 1;
233 break;
234 case 'r':
235#ifdef HAVE_POLICY_FWD
236 f_rfcmode = 1;
237#else
238 rkwarn();
239#endif
240 break;
241 case 'k':
242#ifdef HAVE_POLICY_FWD
243 f_rfcmode = 0;
244#else
245 rkwarn();
246#endif
247 break;
248 case 'V':
249 usage(1);
250 break;
251#ifndef __NetBSD__
252 case 'h':
253#endif
254 case '?':
255 default:
256 usage(0);
257 }
258 }
259
260 argc -= optind;
261 argv += optind;
262
263 if (argc > 0) {
264 while (argc--) {
265 if (fileproc(*argv++) < 0) {
266 err(1, "%s", argv[-1]);
267 }
268 }
269 exit(0);
270 }
271
272 so = pfkey_open();
273 if (so < 0) {
274 perror("pfkey_open");
275 exit(1);
276 }
277
278 switch (f_mode) {
279 case MODE_CMDDUMP:
280 sendkeyshort(f_policy ? SADB_X_SPDDUMP : SADB_DUMP);
281 break;
282 case MODE_CMDFLUSH:
283 sendkeyshort(f_policy ? SADB_X_SPDFLUSH: SADB_FLUSH);
284 break;
285 case MODE_SCRIPT:
286 if (get_supported() < 0) {
287 errx(1, "%s", ipsec_strerror());
288 }
289 if (parse(&fp))
290 exit(1);
291 break;
292 case MODE_STDIN:
293 if (get_supported() < 0) {
294 errx(1, "%s", ipsec_strerror());
295 }
296 stdin_loop();
297 break;
298 case MODE_PROMISC:
299 promisc();
300 /* NOTREACHED */
301 default:
302 usage(0);
303 }
304
305 exit(0);
306}
307
308static int
309get_supported(void)
310{
311
312 if (pfkey_send_register(so, SADB_SATYPE_UNSPEC) < 0)
313 return -1;
314
315 if (pfkey_recv_register(so) < 0)
316 return -1;
317
318 return 0;
319}
320
321static void
322stdin_loop(void)
323{
324 char line[1024], *semicolon, *comment;
325 size_t linelen = 0;
326
327 memset(line, 0, sizeof(line));
328
329 parse_init();
330 while (1) {
331#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
332 char *rbuf;
333 rbuf = readline("");
334 if (!rbuf)
335 break;
336#else
337 char rbuf[1024];
338 rbuf[0] = '\0';
339 if (fgets(rbuf, sizeof(rbuf), stdin) == NULL)
340 break;
341 if (rbuf[strlen(rbuf)-1] == '\n')
342 rbuf[strlen(rbuf)-1] = '\0';
343#endif
344 comment = strchr(rbuf, '#');
345 if (comment)
346 *comment = '\0';
347
348 if (!rbuf[0])
349 continue;
350
351 linelen += snprintf(&line[linelen], sizeof(line) - linelen,
352 "%s%s", linelen > 0 ? " " : "", rbuf);
353
354 semicolon = strchr(line, ';');
355 while (semicolon) {
356 char saved_char = *++semicolon;
357 *semicolon = '\0';
358#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
359 add_history(line);
360#endif
361
362#ifdef HAVE_PFKEY_POLICY_PRIORITY
363 last_msg_type = -1; /* invalid message type */
364#endif
365
366 parse_string(line);
367 if (exit_now)
368 return;
369 if (saved_char) {
370 *semicolon = saved_char;
371 linelen = strlen(semicolon);
372 memmove(line, semicolon, linelen + 1);
373 semicolon = strchr(line, ';');
374 } else {
375 semicolon = NULL;
376 linelen = 0;
377 }
378 }
379 }
380}
381
382static void
383sendkeyshort(u_int type)
384{
385 struct sadb_msg msg;
386
387 msg.sadb_msg_version = PF_KEY_V2;
388 msg.sadb_msg_type = type;
389 msg.sadb_msg_errno = 0;
390 msg.sadb_msg_satype = SADB_SATYPE_UNSPEC;
391 msg.sadb_msg_len = PFKEY_UNIT64(sizeof(msg));
392 msg.sadb_msg_reserved = 0;
393 msg.sadb_msg_seq = 0;
394 msg.sadb_msg_pid = getpid();
395
396 sendkeymsg((char *)&msg, sizeof(msg));
397}
398
399static void __dead
400promisc(void)
401{
402 struct sadb_msg msg;
403 u_char rbuf[1024 * 32]; /* XXX: Enough ? Should I do MSG_PEEK ? */
404 ssize_t l;
405
406 msg.sadb_msg_version = PF_KEY_V2;
407 msg.sadb_msg_type = SADB_X_PROMISC;
408 msg.sadb_msg_errno = 0;
409 msg.sadb_msg_satype = 1;
410 msg.sadb_msg_len = PFKEY_UNIT64(sizeof(msg));
411 msg.sadb_msg_reserved = 0;
412 msg.sadb_msg_seq = 0;
413 msg.sadb_msg_pid = getpid();
414
415 if ((l = send(so, &msg, sizeof(msg), 0)) < 0) {
416 err(1, "send");
417 }
418
419 while (1) {
420 struct sadb_msg *base;
421
422 if ((l = recv(so, rbuf, sizeof(*base), MSG_PEEK)) < 0) {
423 err(1, "recv");
424 }
425
426 if (l != sizeof(*base))
427 continue;
428
429 base = (struct sadb_msg *)rbuf;
430 if ((l = recv(so, rbuf, PFKEY_UNUNIT64(base->sadb_msg_len),
431 0)) < 0) {
432 err(1, "recv");
433 }
434 printdate();
435 if (f_hexdump) {
436 int i;
437 for (i = 0; i < l; i++) {
438 if (i % 16 == 0)
439 printf("%08x: ", i);
440 printf("%02x ", rbuf[i] & 0xff);
441 if (i % 16 == 15)
442 printf("\n");
443 }
444 if (l % 16)
445 printf("\n");
446 }
447 /* adjust base pointer for promisc mode */
448 if (base->sadb_msg_type == SADB_X_PROMISC) {
449 if ((ssize_t)sizeof(*base) < l)
450 base++;
451 else
452 base = NULL;
453 }
454 if (base) {
455 kdebug_sadb(base);
456 printf("\n");
457 fflush(stdout);
458 }
459 }
460}
461
462/*
463 * Generate 'spi' array with SPIs matching 'satype', 'srcs', and 'dsts'.
464 * Return value is dynamically generated array of SPIs, also number of
465 * SPIs through num_spi pointer.
466 * On any error, set *num_spi to 0 and return NULL.
467 */
468uint32_t *
469sendkeymsg_spigrep(unsigned int satype, struct addrinfo *srcs,
470 struct addrinfo *dsts, int *num_spi)
471{
472 struct sadb_msg msg, *m;
473 char *buf;
474 size_t len;
475 ssize_t l;
476 u_char rbuf[1024 * 32];
477 caddr_t mhp[SADB_EXT_MAX + 1];
478 struct sadb_address *saddr;
479 struct sockaddr *s;
480 struct addrinfo *a;
481 struct sadb_sa *sa;
482 uint32_t *spi = NULL;
483 int max_spi = 0, fail = 0;
484
485 *num_spi = 0;
486
487 if (f_notreally) {
488 return NULL;
489 }
490
491 {
492 struct timeval tv;
493 tv.tv_sec = 1;
494 tv.tv_usec = 0;
495 if (setsockopt(so, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO, &tv, sizeof(tv)) < 0) {
496 perror("setsockopt");
497 return NULL;
498 }
499 }
500
501 msg.sadb_msg_version = PF_KEY_V2;
502 msg.sadb_msg_type = SADB_DUMP;
503 msg.sadb_msg_errno = 0;
504 msg.sadb_msg_satype = satype;
505 msg.sadb_msg_len = PFKEY_UNIT64(sizeof(msg));
506 msg.sadb_msg_reserved = 0;
507 msg.sadb_msg_seq = 0;
508 msg.sadb_msg_pid = getpid();
509 buf = (char *)&msg;
510 len = sizeof(msg);
511
512 if (f_verbose) {
513 kdebug_sadb(&msg);
514 printf("\n");
515 }
516 if (f_hexdump) {
517 int i;
518 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
519 if (i % 16 == 0)
520 printf("%08x: ", i);
521 printf("%02x ", buf[i] & 0xff);
522 if (i % 16 == 15)
523 printf("\n");
524 }
525 if (len % 16)
526 printf("\n");
527 }
528
529 if ((l = send(so, buf, len, 0)) < 0) {
530 perror("send");
531 return NULL;
532 }
533
534 m = (struct sadb_msg *)rbuf;
535 do {
536 if ((l = recv(so, rbuf, sizeof(rbuf), 0)) < 0) {
537 perror("recv");
538 fail = 1;
539 break;
540 }
541
542 if (PFKEY_UNUNIT64(m->sadb_msg_len) != l) {
543 warnx("invalid keymsg length");
544 fail = 1;
545 break;
546 }
547
548 if (f_verbose) {
549 kdebug_sadb(m);
550 printf("\n");
551 }
552
553 if (m->sadb_msg_type != SADB_DUMP) {
554 warnx("unexpected message type");
555 fail = 1;
556 break;
557 }
558
559 if (m->sadb_msg_errno != 0) {
560 warnx("error encountered");
561 fail = 1;
562 break;
563 }
564
565 /* match satype */
566 if (m->sadb_msg_satype != satype)
567 continue;
568
569 pfkey_align(m, mhp);
570 pfkey_check(mhp);
571
572 /* match src */
573 saddr = (struct sadb_address *)mhp[SADB_EXT_ADDRESS_SRC];
574 if (saddr == NULL)
575 continue;
576 s = (struct sockaddr *)(saddr + 1);
577 for (a = srcs; a; a = a->ai_next)
578 if (memcmp(a->ai_addr, s, a->ai_addrlen) == 0)
579 break;
580 if (a == NULL)
581 continue;
582
583 /* match dst */
584 saddr = (struct sadb_address *)mhp[SADB_EXT_ADDRESS_DST];
585 if (saddr == NULL)
586 continue;
587 s = (struct sockaddr *)(saddr + 1);
588 for (a = dsts; a; a = a->ai_next)
589 if (memcmp(a->ai_addr, s, a->ai_addrlen) == 0)
590 break;
591 if (a == NULL)
592 continue;
593
594 if (*num_spi >= max_spi) {
595 max_spi += 512;
596 spi = realloc(spi, max_spi * sizeof(uint32_t));
597 }
598
599 sa = (struct sadb_sa *)mhp[SADB_EXT_SA];
600 if (sa != NULL)
601 spi[(*num_spi)++] = (uint32_t)ntohl(sa->sadb_sa_spi);
602
603 m = (struct sadb_msg *)((caddr_t)m + PFKEY_UNUNIT64(m->sadb_msg_len));
604
605 if (f_verbose) {
606 kdebug_sadb(m);
607 printf("\n");
608 }
609
610 } while (m->sadb_msg_seq);
611
612 if (fail) {
613 free(spi);
614 *num_spi = 0;
615 return NULL;
616 }
617
618 return spi;
619}
620
621int
622sendkeymsg(char *buf, size_t len)
623{
624 u_char rbuf[1024 * 32]; /* XXX: Enough ? Should I do MSG_PEEK ? */
625 ssize_t l;
626 struct sadb_msg *msg;
627
628 if (f_notreally) {
629 goto end;
630 }
631
632 {
633 struct timeval tv;
634 tv.tv_sec = 1;
635 tv.tv_usec = 0;
636 if (setsockopt(so, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO, &tv, sizeof(tv)) < 0) {
637 perror("setsockopt");
638 goto end;
639 }
640 }
641
642 if (f_forever)
643 shortdump_hdr();
644again:
645 if (f_verbose) {
646 kdebug_sadb((struct sadb_msg *)buf);
647 printf("\n");
648 }
649 if (f_hexdump) {
650 int i;
651 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
652 if (i % 16 == 0)
653 printf("%08x: ", i);
654 printf("%02x ", buf[i] & 0xff);
655 if (i % 16 == 15)
656 printf("\n");
657 }
658 if (len % 16)
659 printf("\n");
660 }
661
662 if ((l = send(so, buf, len, 0)) < 0) {
663 perror("send");
664 goto end;
665 }
666
667 msg = (struct sadb_msg *)rbuf;
668 do {
669 if ((l = recv(so, rbuf, sizeof(rbuf), 0)) < 0) {
670 perror("recv");
671 goto end;
672 }
673
674 if (PFKEY_UNUNIT64(msg->sadb_msg_len) != l) {
675 warnx("invalid keymsg length");
676 break;
677 }
678
679 if (f_verbose) {
680 kdebug_sadb(msg);
681 printf("\n");
682 }
683 if (postproc(msg, l) < 0)
684 break;
685 } while (msg->sadb_msg_errno || msg->sadb_msg_seq);
686
687 if (f_forever) {
688 fflush(stdout);
689 sleep(1);
690 goto again;
691 }
692
693end:
694 return 0;
695}
696
697static int
698postproc(struct sadb_msg *msg, int len)
699{
700#ifdef HAVE_PFKEY_POLICY_PRIORITY
701 static int priority_support_check = 0;
702#endif
703
704 if (msg->sadb_msg_errno != 0) {
705 char inf[80];
706 const char *errmsg = NULL;
707
708 if (f_mode == MODE_SCRIPT)
709 snprintf(inf, sizeof(inf), "The result of line %d: ",
710 lineno);
711 else
712 inf[0] = '\0';
713
714 switch (msg->sadb_msg_errno) {
715 case ENOENT:
716 switch (msg->sadb_msg_type) {
717 case SADB_DELETE:
718 case SADB_GET:
719 case SADB_X_SPDDELETE:
720 errmsg = "No entry";
721 break;
722 case SADB_DUMP:
723 errmsg = "No SAD entries";
724 break;
725 case SADB_X_SPDDUMP:
726 errmsg = "No SPD entries";
727 break;
728 }
729 break;
730 default:
731 errmsg = strerror(msg->sadb_msg_errno);
732 }
733 printf("%s%s.\n", inf, errmsg);
734 return -1;
735 }
736
737 switch (msg->sadb_msg_type) {
738 case SADB_GET:
739 if (f_withports)
740 pfkey_sadump_withports(msg);
741 else
742 pfkey_sadump(msg);
743 break;
744
745 case SADB_DUMP:
746 /* filter out DEAD SAs */
747 if (!f_all) {
748 caddr_t mhp[SADB_EXT_MAX + 1];
749 struct sadb_sa *sa;
750 pfkey_align(msg, mhp);
751 pfkey_check(mhp);
752 if ((sa = (struct sadb_sa *)mhp[SADB_EXT_SA]) != NULL) {
753 if (sa->sadb_sa_state == SADB_SASTATE_DEAD)
754 break;
755 }
756 }
757 if (f_forever) {
758 /* TODO: f_withports */
759 shortdump(msg);
760 } else {
761 if (f_withports)
762 pfkey_sadump_withports(msg);
763 else
764 pfkey_sadump(msg);
765 }
766 break;
767
768 case SADB_X_SPDGET:
769 if (f_withports)
770 pfkey_spdump_withports(msg);
771 else
772 pfkey_spdump(msg);
773 break;
774
775 case SADB_X_SPDDUMP:
776 if (f_withports)
777 pfkey_spdump_withports(msg);
778 else
779 pfkey_spdump(msg);
780 break;
781#ifdef HAVE_PFKEY_POLICY_PRIORITY
782 case SADB_X_SPDADD:
783 if (last_msg_type == SADB_X_SPDADD && last_priority != 0 &&
784 msg->sadb_msg_pid == getpid() && !priority_support_check) {
785 priority_support_check = 1;
786 if (!verifypriority(msg))
787 printf("WARNING: Kernel does not support policy priorities\n");
788 }
789 break;
790#endif
791 }
792
793 return 0;
794}
795
796#ifdef HAVE_PFKEY_POLICY_PRIORITY
797static int
798verifypriority(struct sadb_msg *m)
799{
800 caddr_t mhp[SADB_EXT_MAX + 1];
801 struct sadb_x_policy *xpl;
802
803 /* check pfkey message. */
804 if (pfkey_align(m, mhp)) {
805 printf("(%s\n", ipsec_strerror());
806 return 0;
807 }
808 if (pfkey_check(mhp)) {
809 printf("%s\n", ipsec_strerror());
810 return 0;
811 }
812
813 xpl = (struct sadb_x_policy *) mhp[SADB_X_EXT_POLICY];
814
815 if (xpl == NULL) {
816 printf("no X_POLICY extension.\n");
817 return 0;
818 }
819
820 /* now make sure they match */
821 if (last_priority != xpl->sadb_x_policy_priority)
822 return 0;
823
824 return 1;
825}
826#endif
827
828static int
829fileproc(const char *filename)
830{
831 int fd;
832 ssize_t len, l;
833 u_char *p, *ep;
834 struct sadb_msg *msg;
835 u_char rbuf[1024 * 32]; /* XXX: Enough ? Should I do MSG_PEEK ? */
836
837 fd = open(filename, O_RDONLY);
838 if (fd < 0)
839 return -1;
840
841 l = 0;
842 while (1) {
843 len = read(fd, rbuf + l, sizeof(rbuf) - l);
844 if (len < 0) {
845 close(fd);
846 return -1;
847 } else if (len == 0)
848 break;
849 l += len;
850 }
851
852 if (l < sizeof(struct sadb_msg)) {
853 close(fd);
854 errno = EINVAL;
855 return -1;
856 }
857 close(fd);
858
859 p = rbuf;
860 ep = rbuf + l;
861
862 while (p < ep) {
863 msg = (struct sadb_msg *)p;
864 len = PFKEY_UNUNIT64(msg->sadb_msg_len);
865 if (f_verbose) {
866 kdebug_sadb((struct sadb_msg *)msg);
867 printf("\n");
868 }
869 postproc(msg, len);
870 p += len;
871 }
872
873 return 0;
874}

900#define STR_OR_ID(x, tab) \
901 (((x) < sizeof(tab)/sizeof(tab[0]) && tab[(x)]) ? tab[(x)] : numstr(x))

903static const char *
904numstr(int x)
905{
906 static char buf[20];
907 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "#%d", x);
908 return buf;

911static void
912shortdump_hdr(void)
913{
914 printf("%-4s %-3s %-1s %-8s %-7s %s -> %s\n",
915 "time", "p", "s", "spi", "ltime", "src", "dst");

918static void
919shortdump(struct sadb_msg *msg)
920{
921 caddr_t mhp[SADB_EXT_MAX + 1];
922 char buf[NI_MAXHOST], pbuf[NI_MAXSERV];
923 struct sadb_sa *sa;
924 struct sadb_address *saddr;
925 struct sadb_lifetime *lts, *lth, *ltc;
926 struct sockaddr *s;
927 u_int t;
928 time_t cur = time(0);
929
930 pfkey_align(msg, mhp);
931 pfkey_check(mhp);
932
933 printf("%02lu%02lu", (u_long)(cur % 3600) / 60, (u_long)(cur % 60));
934
935 printf(" %-3s", STR_OR_ID(msg->sadb_msg_satype, satype));
936
937 if ((sa = (struct sadb_sa *)mhp[SADB_EXT_SA]) != NULL) {
938 printf(" %-1s", STR_OR_ID(sa->sadb_sa_state, sastate));
939 printf(" %08x", (uint32_t)ntohl(sa->sadb_sa_spi));
940 } else
941 printf("%-1s %-8s", "?", "?");
942
943 lts = (struct sadb_lifetime *)mhp[SADB_EXT_LIFETIME_SOFT];
944 lth = (struct sadb_lifetime *)mhp[SADB_EXT_LIFETIME_HARD];
945 ltc = (struct sadb_lifetime *)mhp[SADB_EXT_LIFETIME_CURRENT];
946 if (lts && lth && ltc) {
947 if (ltc->sadb_lifetime_addtime == 0)
948 t = (u_long)0;
949 else
950 t = (u_long)(cur - ltc->sadb_lifetime_addtime);
951 if (t >= 1000)
952 strlcpy(buf, " big/", sizeof(buf));
953 else
954 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), " %3lu/", (u_long)t);
955 printf("%s", buf);
956
957 t = (u_long)lth->sadb_lifetime_addtime;
958 if (t >= 1000)
959 strlcpy(buf, "big", sizeof(buf));
960 else
961 snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%-3lu", (u_long)t);
962 printf("%s", buf);
963 } else
964 printf(" ??\?/???"); /* backslash to avoid trigraph ??/ */
965
966 printf(" ");
967
968 if ((saddr = (struct sadb_address *)mhp[SADB_EXT_ADDRESS_SRC]) != NULL) {
969 if (saddr->sadb_address_proto)
970 printf("%s ", STR_OR_ID(saddr->sadb_address_proto, ipproto));
971 s = (struct sockaddr *)(saddr + 1);
972 getnameinfo(s, sysdep_sa_len(s), buf, sizeof(buf),
973 pbuf, sizeof(pbuf), NI_NUMERICHOST|NI_NUMERICSERV);
974 if (strcmp(pbuf, "0") != 0)
975 printf("%s[%s]", buf, pbuf);
976 else
977 printf("%s", buf);
978 } else
979 printf("?");
980
981 printf(" -> ");
982
983 if ((saddr = (struct sadb_address *)mhp[SADB_EXT_ADDRESS_DST]) != NULL) {
984 if (saddr->sadb_address_proto)
985 printf("%s ", STR_OR_ID(saddr->sadb_address_proto, ipproto));
986
987 s = (struct sockaddr *)(saddr + 1);
988 getnameinfo(s, sysdep_sa_len(s), buf, sizeof(buf),
989 pbuf, sizeof(pbuf), NI_NUMERICHOST|NI_NUMERICSERV);
990 if (strcmp(pbuf, "0") != 0)
991 printf("%s[%s]", buf, pbuf);
992 else
993 printf("%s", buf);
994 } else
995 printf("?");
996
997 printf("\n");
998}

1000/* From: tcpdump(1):gmt2local.c and util.c */
1001/*
1002 * Print the timestamp
1003 */
1004static void
1005printdate(void)
1006{
1007 struct timeval tp;
1008 int s;
1009
1010 if (gettimeofday(&tp, NULL) == -1) {
1011 perror("gettimeofday");
1012 return;
1013 }
1014
1015 if (f_tflag == 1) {
1016 /* Default */
1017 s = (tp.tv_sec + thiszone) % 86400;
1018 printf("%02d:%02d:%02d.%06u ",
1019 s / 3600, (s % 3600) / 60, s % 60, (uint32_t)tp.tv_usec);
1020 } else if (f_tflag > 1) {
1021 /* Unix timeval style */
1022 printf("%u.%06u ", (uint32_t)tp.tv_sec, (uint32_t)tp.tv_usec);
1023 }
1024
1025 printf("\n");
1026}

1028/*
1029 * Returns the difference between gmt and local time in seconds.
1030 * Use gmtime() and localtime() to keep things simple.
1031 */
1032int32_t
1033gmt2local(time_t t)
1034{
1035 register int dt, dir;
1036 register struct tm *gmt, *loc;
1037 struct tm sgmt;
1038
1039 if (t == 0)
1040 t = time(NULL);
1041 gmt = &sgmt;
1042 *gmt = *gmtime(&t);
1043 loc = localtime(&t);
1044 dt = (loc->tm_hour - gmt->tm_hour) * 60 * 60 +
1045 (loc->tm_min - gmt->tm_min) * 60;
1046
1047 /*
1048 * If the year or julian day is different, we span 00:00 GMT
1049 * and must add or subtract a day. Check the year first to
1050 * avoid problems when the julian day wraps.
1051 */
1052 dir = loc->tm_year - gmt->tm_year;
1053 if (dir == 0)
1054 dir = loc->tm_yday - gmt->tm_yday;
1055 dt += dir * 24 * 60 * 60;
1056
1057 return dt;
1058}
